---
description: Forbid hard-coded natural-language intent detection in the orchestrator
globs: src/orchestrator/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# No Hard-Coded Language Routing

- Never detect user intent with regexes, keyword lists, phrase matching, or bespoke natural-language parsers.
- Never route, suppress, or reinterpret agent behavior based on hard-coded wording such as `generate`, `image`, `send`, or similar terms.
- Let the interaction model choose tools through tool descriptions, schemas, and the system prompt.
- If tool calling is unreliable, fix the model, provider integration, tool schema, or prompt instead of adding text-matching heuristics.
- Treat ordinary model text as ordinary chat output. Determine whether work started from actual tool calls and tool results, not from parsing prose.

```typescript
// Bad: language-specific intent routing
const wantsImages = /\bgenerate\b/i.test(text) && /\bimages?\b/i.test(text);

// Good: observe the model's structured tool call
const assignedImages = toolCalls.includes("assign_image_task");
```
